scopecontent.p:
Many of the papers of Sir James Mackenzie are unindexed. The
		  collection consists of correspondence, largely from the 1900s to the 1920s;
		  notebooks; photographs of people and hospital locations; plans; medical journal
		  articles and other printed material; bundles of notes; reviews of his work;
		  assorted cuttings and typescripts. There is also an album of cuttings and
		  notices, and Mackenzie's birth certificate.
